<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-7j2ZHaa6ERJaE6k29jgdEw" name="how_to_adopt_service_realization,_D1tzYGWuEd6Zd-lbA790BQ" guid="-7j2ZHaa6ERJaE6k29jgdEw" changeDate="2009-09-04T21:35:12.906-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Start by reviewing the following key concepts and tasks:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.tech.common.extend_supp_soa-ibm/guidances/concepts/service_component_54F50804.html&quot; guid=&quot;_Gcmp8GZaEd65K8S2sWS35w&quot;>Service Component&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.tech.common.extend_supp_soa-ibm/guidances/concepts/functional_component_595EAFE6.html&quot; guid=&quot;_Ocmr0GWpEd6Zd-lbA790BQ&quot;>Functional Component&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.tech.common.extend_supp_soa-ibm/guidances/concepts/technical_component_D89DA554.html&quot; guid=&quot;_RjrxgGWpEd6Zd-lbA790BQ&quot;>Technical Component&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../practice.tech.soma.service_realization.base-ibm/tasks/document_service_realization_decisions_FBBF29EC.html&quot; guid=&quot;_3ad-MGWuEd6Zd-lbA790BQ&quot;>Document Service Realization Decisions&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    These will introduce you to the basics of what you need to know about service realization.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p> After reviewing those topics, you can review the tasks, concepts,&amp;nbsp;guidelines, &#xD;
  and work products&amp;nbsp;associated with the practice. &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p> If you are primarily interested in realizing information services, focus on &#xD;
  this task: &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../practice.tech.soma.service_realization.base-ibm/tasks/document_information_service_realization_decisions_CBB72ED.html&quot; guid=&quot;_5q5TQGWvEd6Zd-lbA790BQ&quot;>Document Information Service Realization Decisions&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If you are mainly interested in understanding how to realize the Service Components layer, focus on this task:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../practice.tech.soma.service_realization.base-ibm/tasks/detail_the_service_components_layer_6B4CBADC.html&quot; guid=&quot;_zandcGWuEd6Zd-lbA790BQ&quot;>Detail the Service Components Layer&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3> &lt;strong>Common pitfalls&lt;/strong> &lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p> Successful execution of this practice is made more difficult if organizations &#xD;
  service-enable existing assets without due consideration of the service interfaces &#xD;
  that are needed to support the business.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p> It is easy to focus on service function and neglect nonfunctional aspects &#xD;
  of the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.tech.common.extend_supp_soa-ibm/guidances/concepts/service_interface_soaml_CA95983A.html&quot; guid=&quot;_N5e2oFbBEd6MCpkuB85p5g&quot;>service &#xD;
  specification&lt;/a>, such as performance and scalability. The &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../practice.tech.soma.service_realization.base-ibm/tasks/perform_detailed_technical_feasibility_exploration_9C9527EB.html&quot; guid=&quot;_ysJ_gGWvEd6Zd-lbA790BQ&quot;>Perform Detailed Technical Feasibility Exploration&lt;/a> task is provided to mitigate &#xD;
  this risk. &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p> With respect to information services, a common pitfall is to establish one-to-one &#xD;
  correspondence between data management services and data elements (for example, &#xD;
  mapping each service to a single table in a relational database). This often &#xD;
  results in excess data access operations. It is often better to have each service &#xD;
  mapped a multiple data elements that have strong affinity with each other. &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3> &lt;strong>Measures of success&lt;/strong> &lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        A realization strategy has been defined and documented for each service component.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &#xD;
  &lt;li> Each realization meets or exceeds the nonfunctional requirements for the &#xD;
    service component that it realizes. &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Each component involved in realizing each service has been allocated to an appropriate architectural layer.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
